Major News Items in Leading U.S. Newspapers
WASHINGTON , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading U.S. newspapers Sunday .
The Washington Post :
-- While Judiciary Committee Republicans push for articles of impeachment against President Clinton , most other House Republicans appear torn by the decision or eager to find a way out of the thicket .
-- Confronted by renewed Iraqi defiance , United Nations arms inspectors see little prospect of achieving the results .
The New York Times :
-- President Clinton made an unusual direct appeal to North Korea to set aside any nuclear ambitions in favor of strengthening ties to South Korea and the United States .
-- The killing of Galina V. Starovoitova , a defender of democratic reforms , unsettled old allies , who claimed her as the latest victim of Russia 's lethally corrupt political climate .
